Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.10,0:00:06.10,forest title KB,,0,0,0,,FABLES \N of the\NGREEN FOREST
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.10,0:00:04.03,forest ep title C,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&HFFFFFF&}Today's episode:\N{\c&H25CE1D&}"Paddy Beaver comes to the Green Forest"{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.03,0:00:06.13,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Come on, sunshine,\Nwhat a beauty!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.13,0:00:09.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy must have good news,\Nhe's usually hullabalooing about trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.64,0:00:21.63,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's great to be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.08,0:00:35.38,forest default C,,0,0,0,,What's going on, Johnny?!\NWhy are you yodeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.73,0:00:38.10,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess I'm in love with my echo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.24,0:01:07.02,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Johnny, wake up!\NWake up, Johnny, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.89,0:01:10.89,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hmm. What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.69,0:01:14.62,forest default C,,0,0,0,,The Laughing Brook stopped\Nmaking the sound of laughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.63,0:01:15.63,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.25,0:01:19.22,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Johnny... now listen carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.81,0:01:25.88,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You're right, Polly,\Nwhat's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.54,0:01:29.54,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- It's really strange!\N- Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.92,0:01:30.92,forest default C,,0,0,0,,It's eerie...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.69,0:01:52.69,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.38,0:01:59.57,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, that hurt,\Nwhere is the water?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.48,0:02:03.78,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Holy frog!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.82,0:02:09.02,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I suggest you not use my name in vain!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.32,0:02:14.78,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Look how big the waterlevel fell,\Nthere were tonnes of water here yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.44,0:02:19.76,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, smart as I am I simply can't figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.93,0:02:44.82,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be! What happened?!\NThe brook disappeared!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.09,0:03:01.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,How can we, creatures, exist without the brook,\NHarry? I mean, we need it. What'll we do, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.18,0:03:06.61,forest default C,,0,0,0,,When all is lost, Joe,\Nwe can migrate to the Big River!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.75,0:03:13.45,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's fair, we otters have been living\Nat the Laughing Brook and Smiling Pool
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.45,0:03:15.07,forest default C,,0,0,0,,since my great-grandfather's times!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:19.15,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But you often make long excursions\Nand disappear for a long time, Joe!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.15,0:03:22.99,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You know, I love to travel,\Nit really broadens the mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.99,0:03:27.45,forest default C,,0,0,0,,It's exciting to explore a new river\Nor blue lake...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.45,0:03:31.34,forest default C,,0,0,0,,...but I've always returned here,\Nisn't that right, Harry, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.34,0:03:32.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's right, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.77,0:03:35.49,forest default C,,0,0,0,,It's said, "Home is where the heart is."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.50,0:03:38.22,forest default C,,0,0,0,,And my heart belongs\Nto the Laughing Brook and Smiling Pool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.28,0:03:41.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,To me it's almost like losing a personal friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.26,0:03:45.09,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh...! Oh, all this reminds me\Nof a beautiful saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.09,0:03:49.92,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"A true good friendhip is like the sun,\NYou never miss it till it's gone!"{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:51.62,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Fathers, chapter 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.89,0:04:01.73,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Such a sparkling stream,\Nthe Laughing Brook flows with happiness!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.73,0:04:03.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Johnny, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.89,0:04:08.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I wonder how could a body of running water\Ndisappear over night!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.07,0:04:11.88,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'd sure like the answer to that question!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.54,0:04:15.85,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, mother, there's an answer to every question,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:17.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,just like every cause has an effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:22.58,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I mean, the whole things must follow logically,\Njust like summer follows the spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.87,0:04:23.87,forest default C,,0,0,0,,The spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.30,0:04:25.30,forest default C,,0,0,0,,The spring...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.30,0:04:27.88,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's elementary, my dear friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.88,0:04:30.78,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But as I live, I wonder\Nat the balance of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.73,0:04:32.68,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Every spring has its source,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.68,0:04:36.21,forest default C,,0,0,0,,in this case, the water from the spring\Npours in the Laughing Brook.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.73,0:04:39.87,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Make sense, Johnny!\N- Let's go right to the spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.95,0:04:47.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's a sensible idea, maybe the brook\Nreversed its flow and returned to the spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.78,0:04:53.23,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Boy, when I talk about water\NI become very thirsty, so... pardon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.20,0:05:03.40,forest lyrics C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So they shortcut through the forest,\NAnd they headed for the spring,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:06.98,forest lyrics C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They resolve to solve the puzzle,\NOf the brook's meandering.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:11.43,forest lyrics C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then Harry was distracted,\NBy the sight of something cool,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.43,0:05:14.64,forest lyrics C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And he made a hasty beeline,\NTo a tempting forest pool.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.28,0:05:32.28,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:35.02,forest default C,,0,0,0,,The brook disappears downstream!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.16,0:05:36.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:38.74,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Let's go and find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:39.88,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Yes!\N- Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:42.42,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hurry, Johnny!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:46.62,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Uh-hu, hurry, Joe!\N- I am, fast as I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.71,0:05:52.76,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Through the forest and the lee,\NWent the worried, puzzled three.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.00,0:05:56.89,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Flowers blooming everywhere,\NEven water flowing there.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.92,0:06:01.18,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As they near the forest spring,\NThey heard its water gurgling.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.18,0:06:05.80,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then all at once to their surprise,\NA strange new sight came to their eyes.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.42,0:06:08.42,forest default C,,0,0,0,,What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.66,0:06:10.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Huh, what is what?\NWhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:11.80,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Can't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.45,0:06:15.96,forest default C,,0,0,0,,By the edge of the pond!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.04,0:06:17.91,forest default C,,0,0,0,,No, I'm nearsighted!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.91,0:06:19.72,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- He is?\N- So he says!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.38,0:06:46.52,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Somebody build this! This log's been cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.85,0:06:48.51,forest default C,,0,0,0,,There's no human odour!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:56.95,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I wonder who could've build this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.84,0:07:04.99,forest default C,,0,0,0,,And for what earthly reason?\NIt's a terrible thing to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.71,0:07:08.71,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Look out!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.79,0:07:13.79,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, help!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.17,0:07:28.12,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Dreadful... awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.09,0:07:36.92,forest default C,,0,0,0,,No one's safe anymore,\Nnot even in the Green... Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.87,0:07:39.09,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That is distressing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.94,0:07:43.58,forest default C,,0,0,0,,How could such a strong tree tumble over?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.25,0:07:46.33,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Greetings, good friends!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.61,0:07:49.64,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm Paddy, the busy beaver!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.89,0:07:52.48,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Welcome, folks!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.48,0:07:53.83,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Thank you!\N- Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.10,0:07:58.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow, I'm pleased with myself!\NI cut this tree down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:01.07,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh!\N- Look! Easy as pie!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.74,0:08:12.15,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Amazing!\N- It's remarcable!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:17.16,forest default C,,0,0,0,,This is a mouth made beaver dam!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.16,0:08:18.33,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Beaver dam?!\N- Beaver dam?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.86,0:08:22.19,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right!\NA genuine aspen beaver dam!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.19,0:08:27.55,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'm going to build my home right here in the\NGreen Forest, and this dam is the first step.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.80,0:08:30.07,forest default C,,0,0,0,,How do you like my new home?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.77,0:08:34.20,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's incredible!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.32,0:08:38.64,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- You did this all alone?\N{\i1}- Yep. Sure did. How do you like it?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.26,0:08:44.37,forest default C,,0,0,0,,What about this ridiculous dam, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.58,0:08:46.55,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Just look at this brook!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.57,0:08:51.12,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I swear I'm gonna wreck\Nyour dam right now, Beaver!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.60,0:08:54.69,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I mean, why can't beavers learn to let live?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.69,0:08:56.71,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna wreck it, if it's the last thing I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.59,0:09:06.73,forest default C,,0,0,0,,And furthermore... uh... you...\Nyou one jamming trouble maker!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.73,0:09:09.40,forest default C,,0,0,0,,What about the ecology?\NJust look at this river!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:16.39,forest default C,,0,0,0,,And what's more, I don't think I like beavers!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.24,0:09:29.78,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Laughing Brook is shedding tears,\NThe Smiling Pool is scowling,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.78,0:09:34.75,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The forest folk are filled with fears,\NThe frightened wind is howling.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.99,0:09:41.93,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Scoop, scoop, I've been scoop...\Nwhat big mouths talk about the beaver!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.72,0:09:46.22,forest default C,,0,0,0,,They don't call me Blabbing Blue Jay for nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.31,0:09:53.07,forest default C,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of things\Nwe hear about before you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:58.15,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I don't know about you squirells getting the news\Nfirst, but when you birds beat me to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.39,0:10:00.19,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Chirp, chirp, be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.85,0:10:30.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Now, watch this closely!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.80,0:10:39.03,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.55,0:10:42.96,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Don't be afraid!\NI've thought of practically everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.65,0:10:45.57,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Look, I've even build a canal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:49.35,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I planned it so the tree will fall\Nin the canal and not on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.35,0:10:52.61,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh, is that how it works?\N- Where did you learn such things?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.84,0:10:57.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,My mummy and my daddy taught me.\NThey learned it from my grandma and my grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.77,0:11:00.02,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I think it's something called heredity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.49,0:11:02.29,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Aha... true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.67,0:11:03.52,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.52,0:11:06.71,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You, beavers, call it heredity,\Nbut woodchucks call it instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.98,0:11:09.65,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Tell me, if you didn't do\Nexactly as you were taught,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.65,0:11:12.33,forest default C,,0,0,0,,didn't your daddy give you\Na nasty bite on the ear?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.33,0:11:15.76,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Absolutely!\NI can still feel the pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.12,0:11:17.85,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Not me!\N- Ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.51,0:11:22.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh, come on!\N- My folks never bit me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.36,0:11:24.31,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But when I forgot what they taught me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.31,0:11:27.53,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I was spanked\Nand I'm embarrassed to tell you where!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.41,0:11:30.87,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I think I can guess!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.45,0:11:33.69,forest default C,,0,0,0,,We know too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.95,0:11:35.73,forest default C,,0,0,0,,We know too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.58,0:11:38.61,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm glad you're all here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.16,0:11:43.54,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm gonna make some straight poles.\NStand by and watch a genius at work!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:50.45,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hey...! Duper, thief, burglar, bandit, thief!\NWhat's wrong with you, anyway, thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.10,0:11:59.17,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Thief!\N- Mister Jay, who are you calling a thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.58,0:12:02.06,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Could it be you're referring to yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.93,0:12:11.93,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's right, laugh, you foolish animals!\NYou thief, thief, thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.93,0:12:17.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You bandit, thief, look what you've done!\NYou thief! Why...?! Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.57,0:12:23.35,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Thief, thief, thief, why, look what you've done!\N- Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.35,0:12:26.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Thief... Why you...\N- Mister Jay, you're crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.94,0:12:29.70,forest default C,,0,0,0,,His behavior is for the birds!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.70,0:12:33.52,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy always act that way,\Nhe is happiest when he is miserable!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:38.00,forest default C,,0,0,0,,And when is miserable he's absolutely ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.00,0:12:42.29,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Our friend Sammy is even-tempered,\Nhe's contemptible all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.99,0:12:53.70,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Thief, thief! Why can't you see what he's done,\Nlook at this, thief, thief! Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.70,0:12:55.87,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I am not a thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:13:00.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, look what you've done!\NYou've stolen our trees! Thief! Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.87,0:13:08.68,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I insist, if he destroys our trees,\Ndoesn't that make him a thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.03,0:13:10.03,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hmm... hmm... true...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.35,0:13:11.45,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Joe and Harry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.74,0:13:15.39,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Sammy's right, I think he's right!\N- Please, Joe, listen to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.16,0:13:19.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.61,0:13:22.71,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Don't you often do things\Nbecause they were taught to you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.72,0:13:25.33,forest default C,,0,0,0,,by your mother and father, don't you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.91,0:13:29.77,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Oh!\N- Well, do you agree or don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.81,0:13:33.03,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I agree. I was soundly spanked by my father
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.03,0:13:35.09,forest default C,,0,0,0,,when I forgot the things he taught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.23,0:13:38.08,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, Paddy had his ears chewed seven times
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.08,0:13:40.15,forest default C,,0,0,0,,till he learned how to cut trees\Nand build a dam!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.21,0:13:42.53,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But what will become of the Laughing Brook?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.53,0:13:46.40,forest default C,,0,0,0,,It no longer sings joyfully,\Nthe silence is maddening!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.41,0:13:49.96,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but without the Laughing Brook,\Nthe Green Forest will become a desert!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.96,0:13:53.43,forest default C,,0,0,0,,We'll have to move far away,\Nto the Big River, and live there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.43,0:13:57.63,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- I-I-I don't want to move...!\N- Neither do I!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.08,0:14:05.10,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Return the Laughing Brook to us,\Nrestore happiness!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.39,0:14:10.97,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's right, return the water, restore the trees!\NThief, thief, you thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.21,0:14:13.43,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Joe, Harry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.83,0:14:14.83,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Johnny, Polly!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:18.07,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Please, have faith in me! Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:20.56,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I promise the brook will live as it did before!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.64,0:14:21.79,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Really?! But how?!\N- Really?! But how?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.03,0:14:26.29,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You're not going to destroy the dam\Nafter all the trouble you went through building it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.70,0:14:28.89,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Certainly not!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.49,0:14:33.03,forest default C,,0,0,0,,In a few days, the dam\Nwill be brimming with water
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.03,0:14:36.64,forest default C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and the Laughing Brook will return\Nmore joyful then ever!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.67,0:14:39.27,forest default C,,0,0,0,,It's-it's hard to believe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.62,0:14:42.68,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I feel that Paddy is telling the truth,\Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.68,0:14:45.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Of course I'm telling the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.26,0:14:47.84,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Cross your heart?\N- On my honour!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.84,0:14:52.49,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You're not a bad guy after all and we\Nwon't have to move from the Green Forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.49,0:14:55.02,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- That's wonderful!\N- How nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.18,0:14:58.05,forest default C,,0,0,0,,No... no... you're all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.05,0:15:00.95,forest default C,,0,0,0,,The nuts and the acorns\Nfrom the trees are our food,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:02.79,forest default C,,0,0,0,,and if we don't have the trees,\Nwe can't eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.79,0:15:05.31,forest default C,,0,0,0,,and if we can't eat,\Nwe're all going to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.35,0:15:09.09,forest default C,,0,0,0,,These trees aren't your personal property!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.36,0:15:16.83,forest default C,,0,0,0,,These trees belong to the Green Forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.83,0:15:19.35,forest default C,,0,0,0,,and the Green Forest belongs to one and all!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.17,0:15:27.67,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You all receive the necessities of life\Nfrom bounties of the Green Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.67,0:15:30.40,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, the trees are necessary to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.07,0:15:34.40,forest default C,,0,0,0,,If you have the right to plot nuts,\Nso I have the right to cut trees!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.40,0:15:36.46,forest default C,,0,0,0,,But, tell me, why did you construct this dam,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.46,0:15:38.89,forest default C,,0,0,0,,and why is this pond so vital to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.02,0:15:41.82,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'm going to build my house\Nin the center of the pond,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.82,0:15:43.83,forest default C,,0,0,0,,it's going to be a kind of pondeminium!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:48.24,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Well, it sounds like a neat house,\Ndon't you think so, Johnny?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:51.78,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I've decided that the Green Forest\Nis the place for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.78,0:15:56.70,forest default C,,0,0,0,,I'm going to plant my roots here!\NAfter all, this is a free forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.74,0:16:00.38,forest default C,,0,0,0,,No-no-no, no one invited you to come here\Nand live in the Green Forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.38,0:16:02.74,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Get out of here, you thief, thief, thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.42,0:16:06.96,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Hi there, Paddy!\N- Oh, no, Paddy, he always speaks before he thinks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:09.26,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Look what he's done to the trees!\NLook!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.45,0:16:12.56,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Sammy's always been rude,\Ndon't worry about what he says, Paddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.56,0:16:15.69,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Sammy never did acquire\Nany of the social graces!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.76,0:16:18.53,forest default C,,0,0,0,,You know, I actually feel sorry for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.53,0:16:20.42,forest default C,,0,0,0,,There's gonna be trouble\Nand I'm gonna cause it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.48,0:16:25.16,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Trouble, trouble, I'm gonna cause\Ntrouble for you, big mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.16,0:16:27.06,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's right, trouble, trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.77,0:16:36.75,forest default C,,0,0,0,,There goes big mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.89,0:16:45.75,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Help, help! Help, help!\NHelp me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.27,0:17:06.48,forest default C,,0,0,0,,That's not funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.74,0:17:17.94,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've got to get busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.30,0:17:27.79,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Day by day, log by log,\NOn from early morn,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.79,0:17:31.42,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Paddy laboured at his dam,\NTill a pond was born.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.00,0:17:59.28,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.49,0:18:09.45,forest default C,,0,0,0,,The Laughing Brook has been reborn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.28,0:18:13.84,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Wow!\NMy, oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.04,0:18:46.04,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Johnny!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.64,0:18:50.68,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- Yes?!\N- The brook, listen to the brook!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:55.36,forest default C,,0,0,0,,- It is the brook! It's beautiful, Polly!\N- Come on, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.85,0:18:56.85,forest default C,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.74,0:19:06.74,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Paddy Beaver did his job,\NA new dam he invented,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:11.26,forest narrator C,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Laughing Brook is back to stay,\NAnd his new friends are contented.{\i}
